# PHP & WordPress Standards

## PHP Version

PHP 8.2+ features are required — use them:

- `readonly` classes for all DTOs (immutable value objects)
- Backed enums (`string` or `int`) for typed constants
- `match` expressions instead of `switch` where applicable
- Named arguments for clarity on multi-parameter calls
- First-class callable syntax: `foo(...)` instead of `fn($x) => foo($x)`

## WordPress Coding Standards

Run `make lint` after every PHP change. This runs PHPCS (`WordPress-Extra` + `WordPress-Docs`) **and** PHPStan at level 8. Both must pass clean — zero errors, zero suppression without a documented reason.

- Short array syntax `[]` always — never `array()`
- Service classes are static-only, named `Telex_*`, one per file at `includes/class-telex-*.php`
- New enums → `includes/Enums/` with PascalCase filenames
- New readonly DTOs → `includes/class-telex-dtos.php`
- New exceptions → `lib/telex-sdk/src/` alongside existing SDK exceptions

## Security — Non-Negotiable

Every single one of these applies every time:

- **Input:** `sanitize_text_field()`, `absint()`, `wp_unslash()` before any use of user-supplied data
- **Output:** `esc_html()`, `esc_attr()`, `esc_url()`, `wp_kses_post()` on every echo
- **Nonces:** verify with `check_ajax_referer()` or `wp_verify_nonce()` on all form/AJAX handlers
- **Capabilities:** `current_user_can()` check before every privileged operation — even if the REST permission callback already checked
- **SQL:** `$wpdb->prepare()` on every query — no exceptions
- **File paths:** validate against ZipSlip and path traversal on any externally-sourced filename; check extension against the blocklist
- **HTTP:** all outbound requests go through `Telex_WP_Http_Client` — never `wp_remote_*` directly; HTTPS only, SSL always verified

## Caching

Use `Telex_Cache::get_or_revalidate()` for all Telex API responses. Never call `set_transient()` / `get_transient()` directly for API data — it bypasses stampede protection and stale-while-revalidate.

## Circuit Breaker

Wrap all Telex API calls with `Telex_Circuit_Breaker::is_available()` before calling and `Telex_Circuit_Breaker::record_failure()` / `record_success()` after.

## Testing

Every new feature or bug fix requires a PHPUnit test:

- Test files: `tests/test-*.php` extending `WP_UnitTestCase`
- Run: `make test` — must pass clean with no skipped assertions
